extra.rawValue: How long is the QR code valid?
extra.raw: 'How long is the QR code valid?'

value.value: How long is the QR code valid?

extra.rawValue: PCR test result is usually valid for 72 hours. However, the time can be changed depending on the site you are trying to enter. i.e. a site manager of a conference event can set the time as 24 hours. This means your test result has to be taken within 24 hour of the time you are trying to enter.

You can only use PCL FREE PASS app on the phone registered in your name. If you are using the same mobile device but have changed your phone number, then please verify your new phone number by PASS app and then re-register using the new phone number.
I want to change my photo
Currently you cannot change your photo for privacy policy. Please make sure you upload a correct photo of your face when you are signing up.
How long is the QR code valid?

PCR test result is usually valid for 72 hours. However, the time can be changed depending on the site you are trying to enter. i.e. a site manager of a conference event can set the time as 24 hours. This means your test result has to be taken within 24 hour of the time you are trying to enter.
How do I register a place?

To register your place, please click site manager->register a place. Please enter the name, address, phone number, applicable visitors and entry period information. You will get notified once your place is registered.
I want to change the information of my registered place.

To change the information of the place you registered, please press the small edit button beside the name of your registered place. It will take you to a new page and you can edit your information from there.
